n id="dpsp-post-content-markup" data-image-pin-it="true"></span>
<p><strong><em>Sandesh (Sondesh) is one of the ultimate Bengali mishti (sweets)!</em></strong><em> This is a foolproof recipe that is nearly impossible to mess up and it makes perfectly sweet and tempting sandesh that are great for festivals, holidays, parties, and gifting.</em></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter is-resized"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-1.jpg" alt="Sandesh Recipe (Bengali Sweet Sondesh)" class="wp-image-39002" width="500" height="750" srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-1.jpg 667w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-1-360x540.jpg 360w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-1-180x270.jpg 180w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /></figure></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">What is Sandesh (Sondesh)?</h2>



<p>In West Bengal it is called ‘<strong><em>sondesh</em></strong>’ or ‘<strong><em>shondesh</em></strong>’ and elsewhere it is called sandesh sweet. <em><strong>It is a dry yet semi-moist dessert that actually will melt in your mouth.</strong></em> This is chenna based sweet recipe just like other Bengali desserts <a href="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/rasgulla-recipe/">rasgulla</a>, <a href="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/rasmalai-recipe/">rasmalai</a>, chum chum.</p>



<p>Not only it is easy to make, but it requires <strong>only 3 ingredients</strong> (that are pantry staples &#8211; milk, lemon juice, and sugar). Yes, no other flavoring ingredient needed, still, it tastes too good.</p>



<p class="has-background has-very-light-gray-background-color">These are perfect for parties or festivals that you can make ahead of time and store in the refrigerator. <strong>Though it is milk-based dessert so it doesn’t keep for long. But stays fresh for 2-3 days only.</strong></p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">3 Ingredients for Sandesh sweet</h2>



<ol class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Milk</strong> &#8211; always use full-fat whole milk (preferably cow’s milk). We will be curdling the milk to separate the fat content. For that purpose, you will need full-fat milk. Low fat, fat-free won’t work here.</li><li><strong>Lemon juice</strong> &#8211; Always use freshly squeezed lemon juice (not bottled one). It is used to curdle the milk. Instead, you can use vinegar.</li><li><strong>Sugar</strong> &#8211; of course, it is a dessert recipe.</li></ol>



<p style="font-size:25px"><strong>The sandesh making process is divided into two parts.</strong></p>



<ol class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Making chenna</strong> &#8211; <em>You MUST make </em><a href="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/chenna/"><em>chenna</em></a><em> fresh and use right away.</em> You cannot make it ahead of time or cannot use a refrigerated one.</li><li><strong>Making sandesh from chenna</strong> (soft paneer) &#8211; it takes some time since the process requires kneading, cooking on stove-top and shaping. Though it takes time, sure it is easy.</li></ol>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">How to make chenna for Sandesh?</h2>



<p>1) <strong>Prepare a sieve for straining:</strong> line a large fine-mesh sieve with several layers of cheese cheesecloth or use man’s handkerchief or thin cotton cloth. Set over a large bowl.</p>



<p>2) <strong>Add milk to a pot and Bring it to a boil</strong>: Pour the milk in a heavy bottom pan or patila. Heat the milk over medium heat and let it come to a full boil, stirring frequently.<br><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-38994" style="width: 400px;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20266'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="boiling the milk" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-1.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-1-340x225.jpg 340w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" data-lazy-src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-1.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-38994" style="width: 400px;" src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-1.jpg" alt="boiling the milk" srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-1.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-1-340x225.jpg 340w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></noscript></p>



<p>3) <strong>Off the heat, add lemon juice:</strong> Once it starts boiling, turn off the heat and remove it from the heat. Add lemon juice and keep stirring. <br><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-38995" style="width: 400px;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20266'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="adding lemon juice" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-2.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-2-340x225.jpg 340w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" data-lazy-src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-2.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-38995" style="width: 400px;" src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-2.jpg" alt="adding lemon juice" srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-2.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-2-340x225.jpg 340w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></noscript></p>



<p>4) <strong>Milk has curdled</strong>: As you stir, you will notice that milk has starts to curdle. If it does not curdle, then you can add more lemon juice. But do not add too much at the beginning. <br><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-38996" style="width: 400px;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20266'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="curdled milk" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-3.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-3-340x225.jpg 340w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" data-lazy-src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-3.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-38996" style="width: 400px;" src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-3.jpg" alt="curdled milk" srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-3.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-3-340x225.jpg 340w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></noscript></p>



<p>5) <strong>Strain the mixture</strong>: You will see the greenish whey and milk solids (chenna) are separated. Drain and separate them using a prepared strainer. You can keep and use the whey later in curry, dal, soup, etc.<br><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-38997" style="width: 400px;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20266'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="chenna and whey are separated" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-4.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-4-340x225.jpg 340w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" data-lazy-src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-4.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-38997" style="width: 400px;" src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-4.jpg" alt="chenna and whey are separated" srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-4.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-4-340x225.jpg 340w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></noscript></p>



<p>6) <strong>Wash under running water</strong>: Then wash the chenna under running cold water, so all the sourness from lemon juice/vinegar will wash away. Also, as it cools down, it stops further cooking and prevents it from becoming chewy.<br><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-38998" style="width: 400px;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20266'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="washing chenna" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-5.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-5-340x225.jpg 340w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" data-lazy-src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-5.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-38998" style="width: 400px;" src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-5.jpg" alt="washing chenna" srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-5.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-5-340x225.jpg 340w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></noscript></p>



<p>7) <strong>Remove the moisture</strong>: Now gather the edges of the cloth, tie and twist, press lightly to remove all the moisture.<br><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-38999" style="width: 400px;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20266'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="removing excess water" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-6.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-6-340x225.jpg 340w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" data-lazy-src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-6.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-38999" style="width: 400px;" src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-6.jpg" alt="removing excess water" srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-6.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-6-340x225.jpg 340w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></noscript></p>



<p>8) <strong>Chenna is ready</strong>: <br><img decoding="async" width="400" height="267" class="wp-image-39000" style="width: 400px;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20267'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="How to make Chenna (Chhena)" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-7.jpg 1000w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-7-720x480.jpg 720w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-7-360x240.jpg 360w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-7-180x120.jpg 180w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" data-lazy-src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-7.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="400" height="267" class="wp-image-39000" style="width: 400px;" src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-7.jpg" alt="How to make Chenna (Chhena)" srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-7.jpg 1000w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-7-720x480.jpg 720w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-7-360x240.jpg 360w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chenna-recipe-7-180x120.jpg 180w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></noscript></p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">How to make Sandesh Recipe?</h2>



<p>1) Take prepared chenna to a plate. <strong><em>NOTE: from 2 liters of milk I got 350 grams of chenna. Depending on the quality of the milk, you will get more or less amount of chenna. So according to how much you get, adjust the amount of sugar in the recipe.</em></strong><br><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-39004" style="width: 400px;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20266'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="chenna in a plate" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-3.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-3-340x225.jpg 340w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" data-lazy-src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-3.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-39004" style="width: 400px;" src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-3.jpg" alt="chenna in a plate" srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-3.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-3-340x225.jpg 340w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></noscript></p>



<p>2)<strong> Knead till smooth</strong>: Start kneading with the help of your palm and keep kneading till it gets smooth and comes together like a dough. You can see the difference from above and below pic. It took me about 4-5 minutes.<br><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-39005" style="width: 400px;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20266'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="chenna kneaded into the dough" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-4.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-4-340x225.jpg 340w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" data-lazy-src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-4.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-39005" style="width: 400px;" src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-4.jpg" alt="chenna kneaded into the dough" srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-4.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-4-340x225.jpg 340w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></noscript></p>



<p>3) <strong>Add sugar</strong>: now add sugar to the smooth, kneaded chenna. If the sugar granules are bigger then grind into the powder and use.<br><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-39006" style="width: 400px;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20266'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="adding sugar" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-5.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-5-340x225.jpg 340w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" data-lazy-src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-5.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-39006" style="width: 400px;" src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-5.jpg" alt="adding sugar" srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-5.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-5-340x225.jpg 340w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></noscript></p>



<p>4) <strong>Again knead</strong>: again knead it well to incorporate the sugar. It will become sticky yet smooth. No more bigger sized milk granules left. Alternately you can do this kneading step in a food processor.<br><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-39007" style="width: 400px;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20266'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="chenna sugar mixture" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-6.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-6-340x225.jpg 340w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" data-lazy-src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-6.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-39007" style="width: 400px;" src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-6.jpg" alt="chenna sugar mixture" srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-6.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-6-340x225.jpg 340w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></noscript></p>



<p>5) <strong>Cooking the mixture:</strong> take the chenna sugar mixture into the pan and turn the heat on medium-low. Continue cooking with stirring constantly.<br><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-39008" style="width: 400px;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20266'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="chenna sugar mixture in a pan" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-7.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-7-340x225.jpg 340w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" data-lazy-src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-7.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-39008" style="width: 400px;" src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-7.jpg" alt="chenna sugar mixture in a pan" srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-7.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-7-340x225.jpg 340w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></noscript></p>



<p>6)<strong> Cook for 4-5 minutes only</strong>: This step is crucial, cook for only 4-5 minutes no more than that. <em>Do not overcook it otherwise it becomes crumbly. We are cooking to get rid of the raw edge of the chenna. We are not looking for any color, texture change.  </em><br><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-39009" style="width: 400px;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20266'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="cooking sandesh mixture" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-8.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-8-340x225.jpg 340w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" data-lazy-src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-8.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-39009" style="width: 400px;" src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-8.jpg" alt="cooking sandesh mixture" srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-8.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-8-340x225.jpg 340w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></noscript></p>



<p>7) <strong>Cool it to warm:</strong> remove the cooked mixture to a plate, spread it for quicker cooling. Let it cool down till it becomes warm.<br><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-39010" style="width: 400px;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20266'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="cooked sandesh mixture" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-9.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-9-340x225.jpg 340w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" data-lazy-src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-9.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-39010" style="width: 400px;" src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-9.jpg" alt="cooked sandesh mixture" srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-9.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-9-340x225.jpg 340w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></noscript></p>



<p>8) <strong>Again knead till smooth</strong>: While it is still warm, start kneading it till it becomes smooth and comes together like a dough ball.<br><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-39011" style="width: 400px;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20266'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="kneaded again while warm" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-10.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-10-340x225.jpg 340w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" data-lazy-src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-10.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-39011" style="width: 400px;" src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-10.jpg" alt="kneaded again while warm" srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-10.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-10-340x225.jpg 340w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></noscript></p>



<p>9) <strong>Start shaping</strong>: now take a small portion and start shaping into a patty or peda like. You can use store-bought moulds to shape them.<br><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-39012" style="width: 400px;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20266'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="shaped sondesh" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-11.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-11-340x225.jpg 340w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" data-lazy-src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-11.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-39012" style="width: 400px;" src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-11.jpg" alt="shaped sondesh" srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-11.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-11-340x225.jpg 340w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></noscript></p>



<p>10) <strong>Garnish:</strong> I have made a design on top and garnished with chopped pistachios. You can use any chopped nuts, sprinkles, mini chocolate chips, saffron as a garnish.<br><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-39013" style="width: 400px;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20266'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="sandesh garnished with pista" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-12.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-12-340x225.jpg 340w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" data-lazy-src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-12.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="400" height="266" class="wp-image-39013" style="width: 400px;" src="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-12.jpg" alt="sandesh garnished with pista" srcset="https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-12.jpg 500w, https://www.spiceupthecurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/sandesh-recipe-12-340x225.jpg 340w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></noscript></p>



<p>These sondesh are perfect for this Diwali festival or Durga puja.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Can I make sandesh with ready-made paneer?</h3>



<p>No, you cannot. You must make fresh chenna. I have seen many makes sandesh from ricotta cheese, though I still have to try it.</p>



